               <p>I live at <placeName id="t17900113-65-crimeloc354">No. 4, White Hart-court, Broadway, Westminster</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17900113-65-crimeloc354" type="placeName" value="No. 4, White Hart-court, Broadway, Westminster"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17900113-65-crimeloc354" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17900113-65-off352 t17900113-65-crimeloc354"></join>; I have had a house there five years; I know the prisoner about seven weeks; he lived with me, and had a one pair of stairs room, ready furnished; there were all the things mentioned in the indictment; they were let with the lodging to the prisoner and his wife; I missed them the 11th of December, they are here; they were pawned: the prisoner was in confinement at the barracks at Knightsbridge; we did not live at that house: on the 11th of December, I discovered the things were gone; I found the woman playing at cards; she went with me; she said she had lost the key of the room; I got a constable and got the duplicates from the woman; it was about ten at night.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17900113-65-person672">
                  JOHN
